<a name="Tag_Cloud_widget" id="Tag_Cloud_widget"></a><h2> <span class="mw-headline"> Tag Cloud widget </span></h2>
<p><code><span style="color: #000000">
&nbsp;<span style="color: #0000BB">&lt;?php&nbsp;the_widget</span><span style="color: #007700">(&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #DD0000">'WP_Widget_Tag_Cloud'</span><span style="color: #007700">,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #0000BB">$instance</span><span style="color: #007700">,&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #0000BB">$args</span><span style="color: #007700">);&nbsp;</span><span style="color: #0000BB">?&gt;</span>&nbsp;</span>
</code>
</p>
<ul><li> widget's classname: 
</li><li> instance:
<dl><dt> title 
</dt><dd> The title of tag cloud. default: <code>__('Tags')</code>
</dd><dt> taxonomy
</dt><dd> The taxonomy the cloud will draw tags from. default: <code>post_tag</code>
</dd></dl>
</li></ul>
